   <body>
      <context>
         <hazardstatement type="danger">
            <messagepanel>
               <typeofhazard>hazard of electric shock, explosion, or arc flash</typeofhazard>
               <howtoavoid>
                  <sl>
                     <sli>Electrical equipment must be installed, operated, serviced, and
maintained only by qualified personnel.</sli>
                     <sli>Apply appropriate personal protective equipment (PPE) and follow
safe electrical work practices.</sli>
                     <sli>Disconnection devices for AC and DC must be provided by others,
be readily accessible, and the function of the disconnection device
marked for its function.</sli>
                     <sli>Turn off all power supplying the UPS system before working on
or inside the equipment.</sli>
                     <sli>Before working on the UPS system, check for hazardous voltage
between all terminals including the protective earth.</sli>
                     <sli>The UPS contains an internal energy source. Hazardous voltage
can be present even when disconnected from the mains supply. Before
installing or servicing the UPS system, ensure that the units are
OFF and that mains and batteries are disconnected. Wait five minutes
before opening the UPS to allow the capacitors to discharge.</sli>
                     <sli>The UPS must be properly earthed/grounded and due to a high leakage
current, the earthing/grounding conductor must be connected first.</sli>
                  </sl>
               </howtoavoid>
            </messagepanel>
         </hazardstatement>
         <note>This procedure is only applicable
to 75â€“100 kVA systems.</note>
         <fig>
            <title>Overview of the Power Connection Assemblies</title>
            <image href="../Images/replace_0n-10800_75-100kw_powerconass_overviewoffass_w120mm_0000192350.png"
                   scalefit="yes"
                   scope="local"
                   placement="inline"/>
         </fig>
      </context>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>Remove the necessary cover(s) in the indicated order, depending
on which power connection assembly to replace.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <image href="../Images/replace_0j-0n10758_75-100kw_sscboxass_remove3covers_w120mm_0000191099.png"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         scope="local"
                         xml:lang="en"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Remove the two screws and slide out the power connection
assembly as far as the cables allow.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <image href="../Images/replace_0j-0p2550_75-100kw_powerconboardass_slideoutstaticswitchpcbass_w120mm_0000192349.png"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         scope="local"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Remove the indicated parts.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <image href="../Images/replace_0j-0p2550_75-100kw_powerconboardass_removepartsonstaticswitchpcbass_w120mm_0000192348.png"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         scope="local"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Note the location of the cables connected to the assembly
and disconnect the cables.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Remove the power connection assembly.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <image href="../Images/replace_0n-10800_75-100kw_powerconass_removepowerconass_w120mm_0000192347.png"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         scope="local"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Reverse the procedure for installation of the replacement
power connection assembly.</p>
         </li>
      </ol>
